description:
Verify session_loader can find files in test fixtures.

**Verification:**
Add temporary test in main.zig:
```zig
const session_loader = @import("session_loader.zig");

// Test with fixtures directory
const info = try session_loader.getSessionFiles(
    allocator, 
    null,  // no project filter
    null,  // no session filter
    .{ .data_dir = "../test/fixtures" }
);
defer info.file_pattern.deinit(allocator);

std.debug.print("Found {d} sessions, {d} agents\\n", .{
    info.session_count, info.agent_count
});
```

```bash
cd zig && zig build run
# Should print session/agent counts matching Node.js
```

**Compare with Node:**
```bash
node -e "require('./src/session-loader.js').getSessionFiles(null, null, {dataDir: './test/fixtures'}).then(console.log)"
```

**Checklist:**
- [ ] Unit tests pass
- [ ] Counts match Node.js output
- [ ] FilePattern.format() produces valid SQL

**Gate:** Do not proceed to M4 until this passes.
